68
00:01:51,759 --> 00:01:54,719
glance you don't really know what your

69
00:01:52,879 --> 00:01:56,638
most challenging task is, take a look at

70
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:58,477
your daily plan and ask yourself, which

71
00:01:56,640 --> 00:02:00,320
of these tasks do I have the most

72
00:01:58,478 --> 00:02:01,998
resistance to starting? As the author

73
00:02:00,319 --> 00:02:04,158
Steven Presfield put it in his excellent

74
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,758
book, The War of Art, like a magnetized

75
00:02:04,159 --> 00:02:07,520
needle floating on a surface of oil,

76
00:02:05,759 --> 00:02:09,440
resistance will unfailingly point to

77
00:02:07,519 --> 00:02:11,519
true north. Meaning that calling or

78
00:02:09,439 --> 00:02:13,759
action at most wants to stop us from

79
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:15,520
doing. We can use this. We can use it as

80
00:02:13,759 --> 00:02:17,118
a compass. We can navigate by

81
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:19,120
resistance, letting it guide us to that

82
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:21,360
calling or action that we must follow

83
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:22,878
before all others. Now, while trying

84
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:24,799
this strategy out might help you be more

85
00:02:22,878 --> 00:02:26,237
motivated in the morning, it also might

86
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:28,079
