93
00:02:36,719 --> 00:02:40,877
productive momentum before they get into

94
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:42,160
the most challenging work of the day.

95
00:02:40,878 --> 00:02:43,999
Now, maybe you're wondering what

96
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:45,359
productive momentum means. And to

97
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,959
explain this, I want to tell you a story

98
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:48,719
about a piece of advice a friend gave me

99
00:02:46,959 --> 00:02:50,399
a few years ago. He told me that when

100
00:02:48,719 --> 00:02:52,399
I'm procrastinating on starting a big

101
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:54,400
challenging task, I should go do the

102
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:57,039
dishes. And the reason for that is that

103
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:59,119
dishes are a chore. They are work, but

104
00:02:57,039 --> 00:03:00,878
they're what he called lowlevel work.

105
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:02,479
Doing the dishes is not a cognitively

106
00:03:00,878 --> 00:03:03,999
demanding task, which means there's not

107
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:05,518
a whole lot of mental resistance to

108
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,359
starting them. But once you get into the

109
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:09,599
