150
00:04:10,959 --> 00:04:14,640
Agile Way and The Productivity Project

151
00:04:12,799 --> 00:04:16,560
called the rule of three. And this

152
00:04:14,639 --> 00:04:18,319
concept advises boiling your daily task

153
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:20,399
list down to the three most important

154
00:04:18,319 --> 00:04:21,758
items that must be done and nothing

155
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:23,278
else. Now, I don't think there's

156
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:25,040
anything particularly special about the

157
00:04:23,279 --> 00:04:26,477
number three, but I do like this concept

158
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:28,319
because it's focused on helping you

159
00:04:26,478 --> 00:04:30,398
narrow that gap between what you plan to

160
00:04:28,319 --> 00:04:32,559
do and what you execute on. Because if

161
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:33,999
you're constantly maintaining this gap,

162
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:35,680
you're waking up every day and you have

163
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,600
this subconscious expectation that

164
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:39,119
you're not going to get done what you

165
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:40,639
planned. And that can only kill your

166
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:42,320
motivation. On the flip side, if you

167
00:04:40,639 --> 00:04:43,759
eliminate that gap and you consistently

168
00:04:42,319 --> 00:04:45,519
do what you set out to do, you're going

169
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:46,960
